I. Problem Statement

The purpose of this project is to develop a CNN-based license plate detection model that can automatically localize license plates in images with high accuracy and efficiency. License plate detection is important in various applications, including traffic management, parking management, toll collection, law enforcement, and surveillance. Manual detection of license plates is a challenging task due to the large number of vehicles on the road and the variability in license plate design and positioning. Manual detection also requires a significant amount of time and resources, which can be a bottleneck in large-scale applications.

II. Methodology

Data collection and preprocessing:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/andrewmvd/car-plate-detection

The 433 images with bounding box annotations which is collected on kaggle will be used for training and testing the model. We will preprocessing the dataset by Resize the images, Normalize the pixel values and Extract the license plate region.

Model training:

For the CNN-based license plate detection model, we will use Convolutional Neural Network architecture. These architecture have shown excellent performance in object detection tasks and have been widely used in the literature. We will experiment with both architectures to compare their performance on our dataset.

Evaluation metrics and validation:

We will use a combination of evaluation metrics and validation techniques to assess the performance of the model. The evaluation metrics that we will use include accuracy, mean_squared_error

In [7]:
from lxml import etree
In [8]:
# extract the size of image
for annotation in glob.glob(a_path+"/*.xml"): #extract xml files
    ETtree = etree.parse(annotation)
    
    # according to tag in xml file, extract the information of img and plate location
    for dim in ETtree.xpath("size"):
        width = int(dim.xpath("width")[0].text)
        height = int(dim.xpath("height")[0].text)
        
    for dim in ETtree.xpath("object/bndbox"):
        xmin = int(dim.xpath("xmin")[0].text)/(width/size)
        ymin = int(dim.xpath("ymin")[0].text)/(height/size)
        xmax = int(dim.xpath("xmax")[0].text)/(width/size)
        ymax = int(dim.xpath("ymax")[0].text)/(height/size)
        y.append([int(xmax), int(ymax), int(xmin), int(ymin)]) # put the plate location information in a list
        
        #get the name of the xml file and find the related img (some pictures have multiple plates)
        data_name=[annotation.split('/')[-1][0:-4]] 
        img_name = data_name[0]
        extension = ".png"
        img_path = os.path.join(i_path, img_name + extension)
        img_path = img_path.replace("\\", "/")
        img1 = glob.glob(img_path)
        img = cv2.imread(img1[0])
        img = cv2.resize(img, (size,size))  # resize the input img into 200*200
        X.append(np.array(img))

In [25]:
# CNN model training
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dropout, Flatten, Conv2D,MaxPooling2D,Dense
from keras import regularizers

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(64,(3,3),input_shape=(200,200,3),activation='relu')) #activation funtion, add convolutional layers
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))         #The pooling layer reduces the data dimension

model.add(Dropout(0.1))                          #prevent overfitting

model.add(Conv2D(32,(3,3),activation='relu',kernel_regularizer=regularizers.l2(0.01))) # apply L2 regularization
model.add(MaxPooling2D(pool_size=(2,2)))

model.add(Dropout(0.2))

model.add(Flatten())                             #two dimensional matrix into one dimension
model.add(Dense(64, activation="relu"))
model.add(Dense(4, activation="sigmoid"))

model.compile(optimizer='adam',loss='mean_squared_error',metrics=['accuracy'])

model.summary()

Conclusion¶

The CNN-based license plate detection model was developed using Keras with two convolutional layers, pooling layers, and dropout regularization. The model achieved an accuracy of 90.83% on the training set and 67.37% on the validation set, demonstrates high accuracy and efficiency in localizing license plates in images, making it suitable for various applications such as traffic management, parking management, toll collection, law enforcement, and surveillance.
